<h2><span><span class="conr">#1</span> <a href="viewtopic.php?pid=2814#p2814">2017-08-03 04:33:43</a></span></h2>
<div class="box">
<div class="inbox">
<div class="postbody">
<div class="postleft">
<dl>
<dt><strong><a href="profile.php?id=9800">Akadine</a></strong></dt>
<dd class="usertitle"><strong>Unconfirmed Member</strong></dd>
<dd><span>Registered: 2017-08-03</span></dd>
<dd><span>Posts: 1</span></dd>
</dl>
</div>
<div class="postright">
<h3>AMD drivers</h3>
<div class="postmsg">
<p>In the documentation here I found a nvidia driver section but not AMD should i use the Open source drivers for Debian 9 Stretch?</p><p>I have an HP touchsmart 300 with AMD Athlon II x2 235e for socket am3. The first step to getting a NextWindow touchscreen to work in Linux is updating the graphic drivers. From what I have put together, this is and older chipset that may only (I could be wrong) be supported by the proprietary AMD driver. </p><p>The proprietary works for Debian 7 &amp; 8, wheezy and jessie, but ParrotSec is built on Debian 9 Stretch which only is supported by the open source driver. Shall I consider my old touchscreen&#160; on retirement until I (doubtful) put windows on this thing? </p><p>Source for my research on AMD drivers, the open source driver page. Link to proprietary drivers is at top right of this linked page:<br/>https:// wiki. debian. org / AtiHowTo</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
